article.headline: Cent. Connecticut St. 88, Sacred Heart 65
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Shemik Thompson scored a career-high 27 points as Central Connecticut State snapped a six-game losing streak with a 88-65 victory over Sacred Heart on Saturday. Chris Baskerville posted his first career double-double, scoring 14 points and grabbing 10 rebounds for the Blue Devils (5-12, 2-4 Northeast Conference). Devan Bailey also had a career-high with 12 points, and Markeys Deans had 12 as well. Leading by just one point early, the Blue Devils used a 15-2 run over a span of 4:44 to take a 28-14 lead with just over 10 minutes to play. During the run, Deans and Bailey hit a 3 apiece and Thompson tallied seven points. The 14-point advantage was the largest lead of the season for Central Connecticut State. Corey Hassan scored 19 points to lead the Pioneers (10-7, 3-3). The teams meet again in Fairfield, Conn., on Thursday.
